`` The terms of that agreement only become effective <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">the date</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">Gulf</ENAMEX> 's reorganization , which we anticipate will occur sometime in <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">early 1990</ENAMEX> , '' said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Lawrence R. Mehl</ENAMEX> , <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">Gulf</ENAMEX> 's general counsel .
In addition , <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">Gulf</ENAMEX> must give the government <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">20 days '</ENAMEX> advance written notice of any loans exceeding <ENAMEX TYPE="MONEY">$ 50 million</ENAMEX> that are made to the <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Bermuda</ENAMEX> - based holding company .
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">Gulf</ENAMEX> 's net worth after those transaction must be <ENAMEX TYPE="MONEY">at least $ 150 million</ENAMEX> .
